definition.value: The pteridine that is lumazine substituted with methyl groups at C-6 and -7 and with a 1-D-ribityl group on N-8.
An amino phenol (one of the three possible isomers) which has the single amino substituent located para to the phenolic -OH group.
An L-lysine derivative that is L-lysine in which one of the hydrogens attached to N(6) is substituted by a methyl group.
